Lunar New Year is a sacred time for many Asian cultures. This year is the Year of the Pig, the last animal in the Chinese zodiac and marking completion of a 12-year cycle. The new year -- falling on February 5 -- brings with it good fortune, as we sweep away the dregs of the past and make room for future prosperity. If you want to get in on the fun, here's a smattering of domestic celebrations ushering in a year of good will and fortune.
